r"""
hamiltonian_riemann.py — Seed-Free Hamiltonian from Riemann Zeros
=================================================================
Implements the seven-step seed-free pipeline from
``sec:hamiltonian_from_zeros`` in theory/iwasawa-tower-zeros.md.

No PySCF, no SCF iteration, no CASSCF orbital gradient.
All four AO integral classes (overlap, kinetic, nuclear attraction,
ERI) are evaluated analytically via the Boys function.  The MO
coefficient matrix C_0 is the core-Hamiltonian guess (J = K = 0,
one diagonalisation of a 4×4 matrix).  CAS(4,4) is a 70×70 dense
diagonalisation.  E_∞ is exact arithmetic from the Riemann zeros.
The Kummer tower then drives E_seed → E_∞ at rate p^{-(k−k_0)}.

Pipeline steps
--------------
S1  Stoichiometric extraction  — m, M, n*, Δt_m, s from MechanismTuple
S2  E_∞ (algebraic)            — E_∞ = −s·γ_1/(n*·Δt_m) [Ha]
S3  AO integrals (analytical)  — S_AO, h1_AO, g_AO via Boys F_0
S4  Core Ham guess C_0         — solve h1_AO C_0 = S_AO C_0 ε, J=K=0
S5  CAS(4,4) diagonalisation   — 70×70 FCI matrix → E_seed
S6  Δ_0 and k_0                — Δ_0 = |E_seed − E_∞|,
                                  k_0 = ⌈2 + log(Δ_0/ε)/log p⌉
S7  Kummer tower               — E^(k) for k = 2 … k_0+K_max

CLI
---
    mqe run --hamzeros --mechanism nitrogenase_lt
    mqe run --hamzeros --mechanism femon2_trimer --basis STO-3G --tower-p 2
    mqe run --hamzeros --mechanism all

Public API
----------
    run_hamzeros_pipeline(mechanism_name, ...) : HamZerosResult
    HamZerosResult                             : dataclass — all outputs
"""

